steps.instruction:
Made by Rick Martinez and can be found [here](https://www.bonappetit.com/recipe/salsa-de-arbol)

### Prep
- Finely grate the garlic

### Steps
1. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium
2. Add chiles and garlic and cook, stirring constantly, until lightly toasted and very fragrant, about 30 seconds
3. Add tomatoes and 1 cup water, increase heat to medium-high, and cook, stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has evaporated and tomatoes are very tender, about 15 minutes
4. Season tomato mixture with salt
5. Using a potato masher, smash until the consistency of a chunky salsa
6. Let cool, then stir in lime juice
